Overview
This project demonstrates how to use SQL for data extraction and transformation and Power BI for interactive dashboards. The goal is to convert raw business data into actionable insights.
Features
- SQL queries for data cleaning, filtering, and aggregation
- Power BI data modeling with relationships and calculated measures
- Interactive dashboards with KPIs, charts, and slicers
- Business insights for decision-making (e.g., sales trends, inventory tracking)


Tech Stack
- Database: SQL Server / MySQL (customizable)
- ETL: SQL queries for preprocessing
- Visualization: Microsoft Power BI
Project Workflow
- Data Extraction: Pull data from SQL database
- Transformation: Apply joins, aggregations, and calculated fields
- Modeling: Build relationships in Power BI
- Visualization: Create dashboards with charts, KPIs, and filters
- Insights: Highlight trends, anomalies, and performance metrics

Example Use Cases
- Sales Dashboard: Track revenue, profit, and top-performing products
- HR Analytics: Monitor employee attrition and workforce demographics
- Customer Segmentation: RFM analysis for targeted marketing
- Inventory Management: Stock alerts and reorder tracking
How to Run
- Clone this repository
- Import SQL scripts into your database
- Connect Power BI to the database
- Load .pbix file to view dashboard

